        *   Process Name: Reimbursement Approval (报销审批).
        *   Logic: Amount > 5000 -> Finance Manager; Else -> Finance Specialist.
        *   This implies: Start -> (Maybe a user task for applicant? Or just start -> gateway?) Usually, reimbursement starts with an applicant submitting. Then a gateway checks the amount. Then different approvers. *   However, the requirement says "Change current process to reimbursement approval". The current process has no tasks. I should design a standard flow: Start -> Submit Task (Optional but good practice) -> Gateway -> Manager/Specialist Task -> End.
        *   Wait, looking at the requirement: "Amount > 5000 add finance manager approval, otherwise finance specialist approval". This implies a decision point.
        *   Assignees:
