            *   Actually, looking at `spelTemplates`, there is `${flowSpelService.findUsersByRole(execution.getVariable("roleKey"))}`. But for static roles like "finance_manager", I can use `${flowSpelService.findUsersByRole("finance_manager")}` as seen in the `amountDynamicApproval` template example: `${execution.getVariable("amount") > 10000 ? flowSpelService.findUsersByRole("finance_manager") : flowSpelService.findUsersByRole("finance_staff")}`. *   So I will use `${flowSpelService.findUsersByRole("finance_manager")}` and `${flowSpelService.findUsersByRole("finance_staff")}`.
        *   Form Type: `dynamic` (from current model context).
